caption: I ordered here for the first and LAST time today. I placed my order and it was confirmed, but when I drove the 20 minutes to pick it up, I was rudely advised that they didn't have my order. As if that wasn't bad enough, they told me it would take too long to make the order and because it was near closing time, they wouldn't. They never even apologized. I would never EVER recommend this place to anyone nor will I ever return to this dump.
First time trying...&  Food was delicious.

Excellent authentic Indian Food. Everything is fresh and this is a true Indian cuisine. We have eaten at EVERY Indian Restaurant in Broward and Palm Beach county. Our go to place used to be Great Indian Grill.. 3 years consecutive .. every Saturday. But they closed and repurposed to fast food. We shopped other Indian Cuisine and switched to Bombay. The Korma and Vindaloo are amazing along with the Saag. You won’t be disappointed!!!

Yesterday, we ordered Vegetarian thali with spice level 8/10 (or 4/5), however we were really disappointed in the quantity we received. All the three curries were not even 2oz in size. The food may have been barely enough for one person for one-time. The spice level was "medium" and not at all "hot", as was ordered. The curries and desert were of the same size.  We have ordered "thalis" from other renowned restaurants as well and in each restaurant the quantity is at least 8oz of curries. For about the same price as Bombay Cafe's, more variety and quantity is provided with the spice level as ordered. This was the worst thali we have had here in South Florida.

It was a let down 😒! I don’t recommend you to eat here.  On our way to the airport, we thought we will have some Indian food and based on the reviews here we stopped at the Bombay Cafe.  The restaurant is a stand alone building and by the appearance and the way it maintained ( from outside look), I should have never gone in there.  They have a modest buffet with few items. 3 items we always look for in any buffet are Chicken tikka masala, tandoori Chicken and nan bread.  So they had all three in the buffet. But the chicken tikka masala was made with dark meat chicken— which is not good. Tandoori chicken was cold. A big no no. Naan bread was ok.  All the other items on the buffet , we didn’t care much.  The entire place need a thorough cleaning. We walked out of that place within 10 minutes of walking in. We smelled like curry chicken.  Buffet cost $10.99. They only serve can sodas no fountain drinks.  So I don’t recommend anyone to go eat here. Sorry I couldn’t take more pictures because we were in a hurry to get out.

My favorite curries here are the okra, aloo gobi, surti dal (yellow lentil) and chana masala. I also recommend ordering a side of roti to go with the curry.
